                            Old home remedies rid readers of colds
                                By Tracy L. Pipp / The Detroit News

What's your remedy for recovering from a cold? Readers share
their secrets:

* "Zinc lozenges and homemade potato soup with kluskis,"
    says N.J. Montgomery of Westland.
* "A nice hot cup of echinacea tea with lemon and honey,"
    says Pat Trotter of Detroit.
* "Lots of vitamin C and echinacea, and comfort food like
    mashed potatoes and hot chocolate,"
    says Connie Butler of Auburn Hills.

The Barnes and Noble gift certificate goes to Ken Kustarz of
Sterling Heights, who says the best treatment for a cold is to
avoid getting one in the first place.
"I used to rest and eat chicken soup and drink liquids, but for the last

10 years I've been eating fresh garlic and cayenne pepper prior to
getting sick and I haven't had a cold since," he says.

